            <h3 data-uuid="80779b80f3cf4a108490b6a88c34c95c">Part 2: Write an Explanatory Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="363dc38debe9416e9d580441ea7815a0">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="47dd5db1a3e44d6c83810937493a6c9a">During
                the Revolutionary War, the Continental Congress passed the Articles of
                Confederation. This document, which established the powers of the national
                government, remained in effect when the war was over. But the government proved
                too weak to deal with many of the issues confronting the young nation. In 1787 delegates from each state met in Philadelphia, and after difficult negotiations
                they drafted a new U.S. Constitution.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="21a5d9712ed94401818980b770f24476">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="751551312aec42f38cd427d5645058e8">The
                Constitution has guided the U.S. government for more than two centuries. Yet
                after it was drafted, a fierce debate erupted over its ratification. Why was
                this document so controversial? Write an explanatory essay about the major
                issues involved in the fight to ratify the Constitution.</p>
            <p data-uuid="7aa5a5458bf84f2cb8d6448d0bdd3f73">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="098b637a923247e584506a552abb9191">
                <li data-uuid="9dba7465f11a4691b688407b8df12d78">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="6c65a35a09514bc1a380714eae64efe4">Use at least <i>three</i>&#160;of the sources in Part 1, and develop the essay with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.</li>
                <li data-uuid="cba974469ad44d6e910d621669cb3262">Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your
                    response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="1a1a6ea2369e46998948f86a9b89841a">Plan
                    your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a
                    concluding paragraph.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="60b6f60f800c4398acf155ea6487c456">Organize your essay in a clear way that focuses on the topic and supports it with explanations and facts.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="48e9229cf46d4f99b5ede97e8cc7e622">Write
                    a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
